  17 def _parents(path):
  18     """
  19     Given a path with elements separated by
  20     posixpath.sep, generate all parents of that path.
  21 
  22     >>> list(_parents('b/d'))
  23     ['b']
  24     >>> list(_parents('/b/d/'))
  25     ['/b']
  26     >>> list(_parents('b/d/f/'))
  27     ['b/d', 'b']
  28     >>> list(_parents('b'))
  29     []
  30     >>> list(_parents(''))
  31     []
  32     """
  33     return itertools.islice(_ancestry(path), 1, None)
  34 
  35 
  36 def _ancestry(path):
  37     """
  38     Given a path with elements separated by
  39     posixpath.sep, generate all elements of that path
  40 
  41     >>> list(_ancestry('b/d'))
  42     ['b/d', 'b']
  43     >>> list(_ancestry('/b/d/'))
  44     ['/b/d', '/b']
  45     >>> list(_ancestry('b/d/f/'))
  46     ['b/d/f', 'b/d', 'b']
  47     >>> list(_ancestry('b'))
  48     ['b']
  49     >>> list(_ancestry(''))
  50     []
  51     """
  52     path = path.rstrip(posixpath.sep)
  53     while path and path != posixpath.sep:
  54         yield path
  55         path, tail = posixpath.split(path)

  58 class Path:
  59     """
  60     A pathlib-compatible interface for zip files.
  61 
  62     Consider a zip file with this structure::
  63 
  64         .
  65         ├── a.txt
  66         └── b
  67             ├── c.txt
  68             └── d
  69                 └── e.txt
  70 
  71     >>> data = io.BytesIO()
  72     >>> zf = zipfile.ZipFile(data, 'w')
  73     >>> zf.writestr('a.txt', 'content of a')
  74     >>> zf.writestr('b/c.txt', 'content of c')
  75     >>> zf.writestr('b/d/e.txt', 'content of e')
  76     >>> zf.filename = 'abcde.zip'
  77 
  78     Path accepts the zipfile object itself or a filename
  79 
  80     >>> root = Path(zf)
  81 
  82     From there, several path operations are available.
  83 
  84     Directory iteration (including the zip file itself):
  85 
  86     >>> a, b = root.iterdir()
  87     >>> a
  88     Path('abcde.zip', 'a.txt')
  89     >>> b
  90     Path('abcde.zip', 'b/')
  91 
  92     name property:
  93 
  94     >>> b.name
  95     'b'
  96 
  97     join with divide operator:
  98 
  99     >>> c = b / 'c.txt'
 100     >>> c
 101     Path('abcde.zip', 'b/c.txt')
 102     >>> c.name
 103     'c.txt'
 104 
 105     Read text:
 106 
 107     >>> c.read_text()
 108     'content of c'
 109 
 110     existence:
 111 
 112     >>> c.exists()
 113     True
 114     >>> (b / 'missing.txt').exists()
 115     False
 116 
 117     Coercion to string:
 118 
 119     >>> str(c)
 120     'abcde.zip/b/c.txt'
 121     """
 122 
 123     __repr = "{self.__class__.__name__}({self.root.filename!r}, {self.at!r})"
 124 
 125     def __init__(self, root, at=""):
 126         self.root = (
 127             root
 128             if isinstance(root, zipfile.ZipFile)
 129             else zipfile.ZipFile(self._pathlib_compat(root))
 130         )
 131         self.at = at
 132 
 133     @staticmethod
 134     def _pathlib_compat(path):
 135         """
 136         For path-like objects, convert to a filename for compatibility
 137         on Python 3.6.1 and earlier.
 138         """
 139         try:
 140             return path.__fspath__()
 141         except AttributeError:
 142             return str(path)
 143 
 144     @property
 145     def open(self):
 146         return functools.partial(self.root.open, self.at)
 147 
 148     @property
 149     def name(self):
 150         return posixpath.basename(self.at.rstrip("/"))
 151 
 152     def read_text(self, *args, **kwargs):
 153         with self.open() as strm:
 154             return io.TextIOWrapper(strm, *args, **kwargs).read()
 155 
 156     def read_bytes(self):
 157         with self.open() as strm:
 158             return strm.read()
 159 
 160     def _is_child(self, path):
 161         return posixpath.dirname(path.at.rstrip("/")) == self.at.rstrip("/")
 162 
 163     def _next(self, at):
 164         return Path(self.root, at)
 165 
 166     def is_dir(self):
 167         return not self.at or self.at.endswith("/")
 168 
 169     def is_file(self):
 170         return not self.is_dir()
 171 
 172     def exists(self):
 173         return self.at in self._names()
 174 
 175     def iterdir(self):
 176         if not self.is_dir():
 177             raise ValueError("Can't listdir a file")
 178         subs = map(self._next, self._names())
 179         return filter(self._is_child, subs)
 180 
 181     def __str__(self):
 182         return posixpath.join(self.root.filename, self.at)
 183 
 184     def __repr__(self):
 185         return self.__repr.format(self=self)
 186 
 187     def joinpath(self, add):
 188         add = self._pathlib_compat(add)
 189         next = posixpath.join(self.at, add)
 190         next_dir = posixpath.join(self.at, add, "")
 191         names = self._names()
 192         return self._next(next_dir if next not in names and next_dir in names else next)
 193 
 194     __truediv__ = joinpath
 195 
 196     @staticmethod
 197     def _implied_dirs(names):
 198         return more_itertools.unique_everseen(
 199             parent + "/"
 200             for name in names
 201             for parent in _parents(name)
 202             if parent + "/" not in names
 203         )
 204 
 205     @classmethod
 206     def _add_implied_dirs(cls, names):
 207         return names + list(cls._implied_dirs(names))
 208 
 209     @property
 210     def parent(self):
 211         parent_at = posixpath.dirname(self.at.rstrip('/'))
 212         if parent_at:
 213             parent_at += '/'
 214         return self._next(parent_at)
 215 
 216     def _names(self):
 217         return self._add_implied_dirs(self.root.namelist())
 218 
 219     if sys.version_info < (3,):
 220         __div__ = __truediv__
